    <sec id="s2_2">
      <title>EMRAE</title>
      <p>Given a phylogenetic tree <italic>T</italic> describing the evolution of the genomes <italic>G</italic>, EMRAE first computes all effective adjacencies w.r.t. <italic>G</italic>. Then, it predicts the rearrangement events for each edge of <italic>T</italic> by means of inference rules (will be introduced in the following).</p>
